1607
02:18:24,903 --> 02:18:30,006
These polls, Mr. President, they talk about cooling fans in residential areas.

1608
02:18:30,427 --> 02:18:33,889
The small wireless facility operator permittee

1609
02:18:34,232 --> 02:18:36,093
shall use a passive cooling system.

1610
02:18:36,813 --> 02:18:47,158
In the event that a fan is needed, the small cell wireless facility operator, permittee, shall use cooling fans with low noise profiles.

1611
02:18:48,919 --> 02:18:52,221
So we all know what that means, low noise profile.

1612
02:18:52,781 --> 02:18:54,762
So they're saying, don't worry about the noise.

1613
02:18:55,582 --> 02:19:01,225
Whatever we do is going to be permittable by whatever standards that are out there, Mr. President.

1614
02:19:01,825 --> 02:19:02,926
But I can guarantee you,

1615
02:19:03,499 --> 02:19:16,829
If you lived within 20, 30 yards of this, and you had your window open in July and August and June, that these low noise profile cooling fans may not be as low as you think.

1616
02:19:17,830 --> 02:19:27,237
So also, it's a concern of a public nuisance, Mr. President, or I should say a potential concern of public nuisance.

1617
02:19:30,060 --> 02:19:45,472
As I allude to the description and the location of these polls say that the community perspective, including visual aspects and proximity to residential dwellings, schools and parks shall be taken into consideration.

1618
02:19:46,073 --> 02:19:53,558
And I hope when our four members get together, the department heads, that that truly is taken into consideration.

1619
02:19:54,019 --> 02:19:56,541
Another aspect of this, Mr. President is

1620
02:19:57,841 --> 02:20:15,947
The petitioner is required to present a written plan indicating the protocol for turning off wireless facilities when utility workers are present on poles in order to limit their exposure to radio frequency emissions.

1621
02:20:16,647 --> 02:20:25,510
The plan should also include a description of any warning signs that will be posted to alert utility workers to radio frequency exposure.

1622
02:20:26,498 --> 02:20:39,188
So this safeguards any utility workers that are going to happen to stumble upon this poll to alert them, hey, we have high radio frequency exposure on this poll.

1623
02:20:39,649 --> 02:20:43,452
My concern, Mr. President, I put this in the form of a motion, as you know,

1624
02:20:44,510 --> 02:20:49,694
The city of Method now owns many of the streetlights, if not all of them, throughout the community.

1625
02:20:50,035 --> 02:20:55,619
There's thousands of them, and there's reasons for our electrical department to be up.

1626
02:20:55,939 --> 02:21:05,066
I know we subcontract the service, but there are reasons for our electrical department to be up around the radio frequency and get exposure, Mr. President.

1627
02:21:05,387 --> 02:21:13,353
And what safeguards do we have, Mr. President, for our city employees for exposure?

1628
02:21:13,869 --> 02:21:26,632
So that is in the form of a motion, Mr. President, to see what safeguards the city has on this, and not just what Verizon is doing for utility workers, but for our city workers.

1629
02:21:27,452 --> 02:21:37,194
And then there should be a written plan indicating the response protocol to be implemented in the event that the equipment is damaged by weather-related event or due to an accident.

1630
02:21:38,114 --> 02:21:41,415
So I think it shows you the serious nature of this equipment

1631
02:21:42,086 --> 02:21:47,268
and the reason why there's protocol set up around it, Mr. President, which is a good thing.

1632
02:21:48,908 --> 02:21:52,109
Then it goes on the interim policy to talk about prohibitions.

1633
02:21:52,929 --> 02:22:02,052
And it says no small cell wireless installation shall be installed on poles that do not meet sidewalk clearance requirements and standards.

1634
02:22:02,492 --> 02:22:07,014
This includes horizontal and vertical clearances for pedestrian passage.

1635
02:22:07,754 --> 02:22:11,575
Applicable requirements and standards may include but are not limited to

1636
02:22:12,418 --> 02:22:14,619
ADA, Americans with Disabilities Act.

1637
02:22:15,319 --> 02:22:23,061
So my other motion, Mr. President, is that has this been reviewed by the city?

1638
02:22:23,821 --> 02:22:34,344
So prior to having a hearing, is the city going out to these sites and making sure that it follows the prohibitions that are set forth for clearance requirements

1639
02:22:35,482 --> 02:22:37,462
